text:
Erika,
Thanks for the note.  Cool work!  Id be happy to guest blog or something similar.  Ive ccd my asst Alex so we can find time next week for a 30 min call.
Thanks
Grant

From: "Erika Bullock (Intern)" <ebullock@ashoka.org<mailto:ebullock@ashoka.org>>
Date: Friday, May 22, 2015 at 7:22 AM
To: "info@codespark.org<mailto:info@codespark.org>" <info@codespark.org<mailto:info@codespark.org>>
Cc: Meera Vijayann <mvijayann@ashoka.org<mailto:mvijayann@ashoka.org>>
Subject: Blogging with Start Empathy


Hi,


Thanks for your response to @StartEmpathy on Twitter the other day! My name is Erika and I am managing the social media for Start Empathy, an initiative of Ashoka<http://www.ashoka.org>.


Start Empathy's goal is to bring empathy, emotional intelligence, and social-emotional learning to the forefront of education conversations; we work with a network of schools who show outstanding devotion to SEL practices, and publish articles and toolkits for a community of educators that follow us on our various networks. If you would like to see more, you can visit our website<http://www.startempathy.org>.


We would love to distribute the work you're doing with kids, coding, and empathy & tech to our networks. Would you be interested in contributing to the StartEmpathy blog, or in cross-posting materials? Your kid-friendly approach to coding is a great example of not only child agency in learning, but also of empathizing with new technologies and learning mediums.


If you're interested, we can set up a call for sometime next week to discuss logistics. I'm looking forward to speaking with you, and hope you have a nice Friday!


Sincerely,

Erika Bullock


Erika Bullock
Media Manager, Start Empathy
Ashoka Innovators for the Public
M: 415-271-0998 S: erika.bullock2
